  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: When users add each other to contacts while being in different networks and after that they both on the same network they are available to send and receive message but see default 3 word usernames and no profile pictures even after updating them after network switch \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUsers A and B see selected profile pictures and usernames of each other\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUsers A and B don't see selected profile pictures and usernames of each other\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices and create 2 users\r\n- As user A (on Mainnet) scan QR code to add user B as a contact and send a text message (user B doesn't receive message from user A and doesn't have a chat with him) \r\n- As user B switch network to Ropsten with upsream RPC \r\n- As user B scan QR code of user A to add him as a contact \r\n- As user A switch network to Ropsten with upsream RPC \r\n- As user A send a message to user B (now user B receives a message)\r\n- As user A change profile picture and username\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly build #350\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
